---
import Streamcard from './Streamcard.astro';
---

<div class="space-y-12">
  <!-- Plate layout: the deployed three-up homepage grid -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">
      Plate layout, three-up (dark middle card)
    </h3>
    <div class="streams-demo">
      <Streamcard
        num="01"
        eyebrow="Owner-builder permits"
        title="Owner Builder courses."
        ctaLabel="Browse Owner Builder by state"
        ctaHref="/owner-builder"
        footnote="Approved by QBCC · Consumer Protection WA · CBOS TAS · Access Canberra"
      >
        Get the training you need to apply for an Owner Builder permit. ABE
        delivers directly in <strong>QLD</strong>, <strong>WA</strong>,
        <strong>TAS</strong>, and <strong>ACT</strong>. For <strong>NSW</strong>,
        where the qualification must be issued by an RTO, ABE delivers in
        partnership with <strong>AlertForce (RTO 91826)</strong>.
      </Streamcard>

      <Streamcard
        variant="dark"
        num="02"
        eyebrow="Site entry card"
        title="White Card construction induction."
        ctaLabel="Find White Card for your state"
        ctaHref="/white-card"
        footnote="Nationally recognised · CPCWHS1001 · Five states"
      >
        The White Card (CPCWHS1001) is the entry ticket for any construction
        site in Australia. ABE delivers online with
        <strong>Blue Dog Training (RTO 31193)</strong> for QLD, WA, and TAS, and
        <strong>AlertForce (RTO 91826)</strong> for ACT and NSW.
      </Streamcard>

      <Streamcard
        num="03"
        eyebrow="Licensed-pro CPD"
        title="CPD for licensed practitioners."
        ctaLabel="Browse CPD courses"
        ctaHref="/cpd"
        footnote="CBOS Tasmania · WA Real Estate"
      >
        Builders, plumbers, electricians, and real-estate agents in approved
        jurisdictions can earn CPD points online. Our library is approved by
        CBOS Tasmania and meets WA real-estate CPD requirements.
      </Streamcard>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Canonical layout: the DESIGN.md §5 transparent 3-column row -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="t-label" style="color: var(--color-ink-3);">
      Canonical layout (DESIGN.md §5): 14rem summary / body / state-nav
    </h3>
    <div class="streams-canonical">
      <Streamcard
        layout="canonical"
        num="01"
        eyebrow="Permit pathway"
        title="Owner Builder"
        ctaLabel="Browse Owner Builder"
        ctaHref="/owner-builder"
        footnote="Source QBCC · CBOS TAS · Access Canberra · Verified 15 Apr 2026"
        states={[
          { name: 'NSW', href: '/owner-builder-nsw' },
          { name: 'QLD', href: '/owner-builder-qld' },
          { name: 'WA', href: '/owner-builder-wa' },
          { name: 'TAS', href: '/owner-builder-tas' },
          { name: 'ACT', href: '/owner-builder-act' },
        ]}
      >
        Get the training you need to apply for an Owner Builder permit. ABE
        delivers directly in <strong>QLD</strong>, <strong>WA</strong>,
        <strong>TAS</strong>, and <strong>ACT</strong>, and in partnership with
        <strong>AlertForce (RTO 91826)</strong> for <strong>NSW</strong>, where
        the qualification must be issued by an RTO.
      </Streamcard>

      <Streamcard
        layout="canonical"
        num="02"
        eyebrow="Site entry card"
        title="White Card"
        ctaLabel="Find White Card"
        ctaHref="/white-card"
        footnote="Source training.gov.au (CPCWHS1001) · Verified 15 Apr 2026"
        states={[
          { name: 'NSW', href: '/white-card-nsw' },
          { name: 'QLD', href: '/white-card-qld' },
          { name: 'WA', href: '/white-card-wa' },
          { name: 'TAS', href: '/white-card-tas' },
          { name: 'ACT', href: '/white-card-act' },
        ]}
      >
        The White Card (CPCWHS1001) is the entry ticket for any construction
        site in Australia. ABE delivers online with
        <strong>Blue Dog Training (RTO 31193)</strong> and
        <strong>AlertForce (RTO 91826)</strong>. Your Statement of Attainment is
        issued by the RTO partner.
      </Streamcard>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  /* Plate cards sit on a deeper ground so the Cream-1 plates read as raised. */
  .streams-demo {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-deep);
  }
  /* Canonical rows are transparent; stack them on the section ground. */
  .streams-canonical {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .streams-demo {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
